title: Sidewall, 1870–90
provenance: From the George Collins house (now Galle or Gallet) in Unionvale, Dutchess County, near Poughkeepsie, built around 1840.
creditline: Gift of Mrs. Adrienne A. Sheridan
description: Aesthetic-style design. Against a light green ground are printed deep red and yellow roses and rosebuds with foliage in a horizontal row. Below, a deep red band bordered above and below with green stripes against which are printed bands of black dot beading.
